
  ---
  SKUEL Architecture Review: UserContext, MEGA-Query & Context Awareness

  Executive Summary

  The architecture has strong theoretical foundations but reveals significant complexity accumulation and DRY violations. The efforts are generally pointed in one direction (user-centric intelligence), but there are opportunities
  for increased focus and cleaner separation of concerns.

  ---
  1. How the Components Work Together

  The Triad Architecture

  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │                          UserContext                                 │
  │                     (~240 fields, THE source of truth)               │
  │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
  │   │  Standard Fields (UIDs)     │    Rich Fields (full entities) │   │
  │   │  - active_task_uids         │    - active_tasks_rich          │   │
  │   │  - active_goal_uids         │    - active_goals_rich          │   │
  │   │  - knowledge_mastery        │    - knowledge_units_rich       │   │
  │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │
  └───────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
                                  │
                                  ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │                      UserContextBuilder                              │
  │   ┌───────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┐ │
  │   │  build_user_context() │  build_rich_user_context()            │ │
  │   │  (1-2 queries, UIDs)  │  (1 MEGA-QUERY, UIDs + entities)      │ │
  │   └───────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────┘ │
  └───────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────┘
