  6. Recommendations

  HIGH PRIORITY

  6.1 Consolidate Context Builders

  Merge the context building responsibilities:

  BEFORE (4 files, 3,200+ lines):
  - user_context_builder.py (1,474 lines)
  - graph_sourced_context_builder.py (613 lines)
  - user_context_service.py (662 lines)
  - user_graph_intelligence.py (675 lines)

  AFTER (2 files):
  - user_context_builder.py (unified building)
  - user_context_intelligence.py (intelligence only)

  6.2 Eliminate get_user_items_in_range() Duplication

  Move to parameterized base implementation. Domains configure via class attributes:

  class TasksCoreService(BaseService[...]):
      _date_field = "due_date"
      _completed_statuses = [ActivityStatus.COMPLETED]

  6.3 Update Documentation

  Sync /home/mike/0bsidian/skuel/docs/architecture/UNIFIED_USER_ARCHITECTURE.md with:
  - MEGA-QUERY pattern
  - Rich context fields
  - build_rich_user_context() API
  - November 2025 changes

  MEDIUM PRIORITY

  6.4 Simplify UserContext

  Consider splitting into composable pieces:
  - TaskContext (14 fields)
  - GoalContext (14 fields)
  - KnowledgeContext (20 fields)
  - UserContext composes these

  6.5 Deprecate Legacy Query APIs

  Mark old methods with deprecation warnings:
  - _query_all_user_context_data() → use _query_user_context()
  - Old build() signatures

  LOW PRIORITY

  6.6 Unify Relationship Service Patterns

  Document clear decision tree for when to use Helper-Based vs Direct Driver pattern.

  6.7 Archive Stale Docs

  Move ~50 completed migration docs from docs root to /archive/migrations_2025/

  ---
  7. Summary

  | Aspect                  | Assessment                                                     | Score   |
  |-------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|---------|
  | DRY Principle           | Significant violations in get_user_items_in_range()            | ⚠ 6/10 |
  | Unified Direction       | Strong - Life Path is clear North Star                         | ✅ 8/10  |
  | Separation of Concerns  | Mixed - Good at domain level, fragmented at user context level | ⚠ 6/10 |
  | Documentation Currency  | 1 month behind, CLAUDE.md is source of truth                   | ❌ 4/10  |
  | Architectural Coherence | Good foundations, complexity accumulation                      | ⚠ 7/10 |

  Overall: The architecture is fundamentally sound but has accumulated complexity over rapid development. The MEGA-QUERY optimization is impressive (10-20x performance), but the code organization hasn't kept pace. The biggest
  concerns are:

  1. 8,380 lines in /core/services/user/ - too much for "context"
  2. 22 implementations of get_user_items_in_range() - clear DRY violation
  3. Documentation drift - CLAUDE.md is accurate, Obsidian vault is stale
